These photos are all hosted on the internet and anyone with an internet connection can access them. If you don't like that, please create and or sign a petition to remove your photo from Winneconne WI Public School Districts and Skyward. These photos are not hosted on this website/document/file. They are hosted on Skyward "https://familyaccess.winneconne.k12.wi.us". Skyward is the website that the schools use to keep attendance, keep grades, and create seating charts. If you take the link "https://familyaccess.winneconne.k12.wi.us/pictures/xxxxxx.JPG?rev=0" and replace the "xxxxxx" with your "student school id" then you will most likely find your most recent yearbook photo hosted online. (Not including senior photos) Your student school ID is the number represented in the barcode on your school ID card (the thing you scan at lunch). If you scan your barcode with a phone app or barcode scanning website, you should find your ID.

This list accounts for the numbers 100000-501000. It accounts for the possibility of 1,000 students per grade level and students up to the future graduation year of 2050. These photos may not account for students' actual grade levels/graduation years, but they are in numerical order.
